up-robert-pattinson-shows-kristen-stewart-around-barnes|title=News Roundup: Robert Pattinson Guides Kristen Around Barnes|first=Fraser|last=McAlpine|date=|website=[[BBC America]]|accessdate=15 May 2019}}</ref>||[[File:Robert Pattinson at the 2018 Berlin Film Festival.jpg|120px|[[Robert Pattinson]]]]\n|-\n|[[Jan Pie\u0144kowski]]||b. 1936|| Writer and illustrator||Lives in Barnes and is a patron<br/>  of the Barnes Literary Society||<ref name=\"Pienkowski \">{{Cite web |url=http://www.barnesliterarysociety.org.uk/about-us/patrons/93-jan-pienkowski |title=Jan Pienkowski  |publisher=Barnes Literary Society |access-date=21 November 2017}}</ref>||\n|-\n|[[Dan Snow]] ||b. 1978|| Historian and broadcaster||Grew up in Barnes||<ref name=\"Nathanson\">{{cite news | title=My London | work=[[Evening Standard]]  | location= London|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/esmagazine/dan-snows-my-london-9610488.html|date=18 July 2014 | accessdate= 22 January 2018|author=Nathanson, Hannah | pages=58}}</ref>||[[File:Dan Snow Aldershot 2019.jpg|120px]]\n|-\n|[[Roger Taylor (Queen drummer)|Roger Taylor]]|| b. 1949|| Musician, singer and songwriter||Lived at White Hart <br/>and at 40 Ferry Road, Barnes||<ref name = \"Queen\"/>||[[File:Queen And Adam Lambert - The O2 - Tuesday 12th December 2017 QueenO2121217-47 (39066610085) Cropped.jpg|120px]]\n|-\n|[[Pete Tong]]|||b. 1960||Disc jockey|||Lives in Barnes||<ref name=\"Jet\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2005/may/22/popandrock | title=Jet Set | work=[[The Observer]] | date=22 May 2005 | accessdate=14 September 2014 | author=Llewellyn Smith, Caspar}}</ref>||[[File:Pete tong head crop.jpg|120px]]\n|-\n||[[Stanley Tucci]] ||b. 1960|| Actor, writer, producer<br/> and film director||Lives in Barnes||<ref name=\"Tucci\">{{cite news | url=https://www.standard.co.uk/lifestyle/stanley-tuccis-my-london-10178904.html | title=Stanley Tucci's My London | work=[[Evening Standard]] |location= London| date=16 April 2015 | accessdate=7 November 2018 | author=Fishwick, Samuel}}</ref>||[[File:Stanley Tucci 2017 Berlinale.jpg|120px]]\n|-\n|[[Julia Watson]]|| b. 1953|| Actor||Lives in Barnes||<ref name=\"Bentley\" /><ref name=\"Wroe\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2011/feb/21/david-harsent-life-writing-poetry | title=David Harsent: A life in writing | work=[[The Guardian]] | date=21 February 2011 | accessdate=18 December 2015 | author=Wroe, Nicholas}}</ref>||\n|}\n\n===Historical figures===\n''Those marked \u00a7 are commemorated in Barnes by a [[blue plaque]]''.<ref name=\"Blue Plaques\">{{cite web|url= http://www.visitrichmond.co.uk/blue-plaques.asp |title=Blue Plaques in Richmond upon Thames |publisher=Visitrichmond.co.uk |date= |accessdate=23 July 2012}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Name !! Dates!!Description!! Notes!!Refs!! Images\n|-\n|Vice-Admiral [[Alfred Carpenter]] {{postnominals|country=GBR|VC}}||| 1881\u20131955|| [[Royal Navy]] officer<br/>and a recipient of the [[Victoria Cross]]||Born in Barnes||<ref name=\"Commander Alfred Francis Blakeney Carpenter\">{{cite web| url=https://livesofthefirstworldwar.org/lifestory/6889414 |title=Alfred Francis Blakeney Carpenter \u2013 WW1 memorial and Life Story |publisher=Imperial War Museum & D C Thompson |accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref>||[[File:Arthur Stockdale Cope - Alfred Francis Blakeney Carpenter.jpg|120px]]\n|-\n|[[Louis-Alexandre de Launay, comte d'Antraigues]]<br/>and his wife, [[Antoinette Saint-Huberty|Madame Saint-Huberty]] || 1753\u20131812<br/><br/><br/><br/> 1756\u20131812 ||De Launay was a French<br/> pamphleteer, diplomat spy and<br/> political adventurer during the French<br/> Revolution and Napoleonic Wars.<br/><br/> Saint-Huberty was a celebrated<br/> French operatic [[soprano]]. ||They were murdered at their<br/> country home at 27 [[The Terrace, Barnes|The Terrace]],<br/> which they had purchased<br/> about three years earlier,<br/> by an Italian servant<br/> whom they had dismissed.